+{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Dp9qZroosvCyB2A76idyJx","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * Shared types for the monorepo.\n     3→ */\n     4→\n     5→import { getUserById } from './user.js';\n     6→\n     7→export type Role = 'admin' | 'user' | 'viewer';\n     8→\n     9→export type Permission =\n    10→  | 'read'\n    11→  | 'write'\n    12→  | 'delete'\n    13→  | 'manage_users'\n    14→  | 'view_reports';\n    15→\n    16→export interface User {\n    17→  id: number;\n    18→  name: string;\n    19→  email: string;\n    20→  role: Role;\n    21→  createdAt: string;\n    22→  updatedAt: string;\n    23→}\n    24→\n    25→export interface CreateUserInput {\n    26→  name: string;\n    27→  email: string;\n    28→  role: Role;\n    29→}\n    30→\n    31→export interface UserFilters {\n    32→  role?: Role;\n    33→  search?: string;\n    34→  limit?: number;\n    35→  offset?: number;\n    36→}\n    37→\n    38→/** Utility to check if a user exists by ID */\n    39→export function userExists(id: number): boolean {\n    40→  return getUserById(id) !== null;\n    41→}\n    42→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01CUr4TuPBBAxbdHAnXKvqjd","session_id":"4893358a-4300-4800-83c4-55e404d61c3d","uuid":"2b0abdaa-ee8a-4650-a6e0-8034d7456ef0"}
