+{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_013vcEQECngCEKEJyvmRry62","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * Worker entry point.\n     3→ * Runs background jobs on a schedule.\n     4→ */\n     5→\n     6→import { Scheduler } from './scheduler.js';\n     7→import { syncJob } from './jobs/sync.js';\n     8→import { cleanupJob } from './jobs/cleanup.js';\n     9→\n    10→export function createWorker(): Scheduler {\n    11→  const scheduler = new Scheduler();\n    12→\n    13→  // Register jobs\n    14→  scheduler.register('sync', syncJob, 60_000); // Every 60 seconds\n    15→  scheduler.register('cleanup', async () => { await cleanupJob(); }, 300_000); // Every 5 minutes\n    16→\n    17→  return scheduler;\n    18→}\n    19→\n    20→// Start worker if run directly\n    21→const isMainModule = process.argv[1]?.includes('worker/dist/index.js');\n    22→if (isMainModule) {\n    23→  console.log('Starting worker...');\n    24→  const worker = createWorker();\n    25→  worker.start();\n    26→\n    27→  process.on('SIGINT', () => {\n    28→    console.log('Shutting down worker...');\n    29→    worker.stop();\n    30→    process.exit(0);\n    31→  });\n    32→}\n    33→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01CUr4TuPBBAxbdHAnXKvqjd","session_id":"4893358a-4300-4800-83c4-55e404d61c3d","uuid":"a85dd618-4012-458c-9ea2-31622c6c96e9"}
